-- Apache, Apple, BP, Cytec Industries, Gilead, Yahoo: U.S. Equity Preview
-- Lu Wang
-- 2010-07-21T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/apache-apple-bp-cytec-gilead-yahoo-u-s-equity-preview.html

          
          
             Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in U.S. trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  
 Apache Corp.  (APA US): The oil and natural-gas producer
agreed to buy  BP Plc  (BP US) assets in North America and Egypt
for $7 billion and said it plans to sell 21 million shares.  
 Apple Inc.  (AAPL US): The Cupertino, California-based
company third-quarter profit that exceeded analysts’ estimates
as customers began flocking to the new iPad tablet computer and
latest version of the iPhone.  
 Cytec Industries Inc.  (CYT US): The U.S. chemical
manufacturer boosted its full-year forecast after second-quarter
profit topped analysts’ estimates.  
 Gilead Sciences Inc.  (GILD US): The world’s largest maker
of AIDS drugs reduced its annual sales forecast after second-
quarter earnings missed analysts’ estimates.  
 Yahoo! Inc.  (YHOO US): The owner of the second-most popular
U.S. Internet search engine reported second-quarter sales that
missed analysts’ estimates as marketers devoted online
advertising spending to rival sites.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lu Wang  in New York at   lwang8@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 20 (Bloomberg) -- Robert Doll, vice chairman and chief equity strategist at BlackRock Inc., the world’s largest asset manager, talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about the outlook for the U.S. economy and stocks.
     Doll, speaking from Princeton, New Jersey, also discusses his investment strategy for emerging market stocks, and China's economy. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                   
    

                 
           
                           
                 
                 
                                       
                                   
               
                        
           
                          July 21 (Bloomberg) -- Philip Orlando, chief equity market strategist at Federated Investors Inc., talks with Bloomberg's Susan Li about his investment strategy for global stocks. 
     Orlando, speaking from New York, also discusses the outlook for the U.S. economy and stock market. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
